OL,6,FWe are standing in the kitchen of the
OL,7,Fflat he rents for #600 per month. His
OL,8,Ffive-year-old son's toys are strewn on
OL,9,Fthe floor of the small living room.
OL,10,FJacob splits his time between Jamie
OL,11,Fand his mum.
OL,13,FJamie is desperate for a two bedroom
OL,14,Fplace so Jacob can have his own room,
OL,15,Fbut he can't afford it.
OL,17,FHe tells me he got a second job a few
OL,18,Fmonths ago, after his outgoings
OL,19,Fstarted to come scarily close to
OL,20,Fmatching his incoming wage.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
