OL,6,FWe meet again later that evening after
OL,7,Fhis shift, at the park, with Jacob. He
OL,8,Fadores his son, and his son adores
OL,9,Fhim. As Jamie pushes his boy back and
OL,10,Fforth on the swings, he explains where
OL,11,Fhis money is going.
OL,13,F"It's enough to survive, but not to
OL,14,Flive," Jamie says
OL,16,F"After bills I think I'm left with
OL,17,Fjust shy of #400 pounds a month, but
OL,18,Fwhen you take in consideration fuel
OL,19,Ffor work and a food shop over four
OL,20,Fweeks. It's gone. Nothing is spare."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/20
