OL,6,FTheir energy bill has since dropped to
OL,7,F#600,000, but having survived that
OL,8,Fenormous jump, they are now facing a
OL,9,Fslowdown in work and jobs are under
OL,10,Fthreat.
OL,12,F"The boys are on hourly rates, so if
OL,13,Fthe work's not here for them, then
OL,14,Fthere's no work for them," says 29-
OL,15,Fyear-old production manager Zac Welch.
OL,17,FThe company relies on housebuilding
OL,18,Ffor many of its contracts, but with
OL,19,Fwork dropping off, they're looking at
OL,20,Fthe possibility of having to make
OL,21,Fseven to 10 men redundant.
